risk for breast cancer. 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   C. STUDY FINDS NO CAUSAL LINK BETWEEN POWER LINES AND LEUKEMIA A
Canadian study suggests that, at least for older children, living
close to power lines does not increase the risk of childhood
leukemia. But the good news does not apply to children diagnosed
with leukemia younger than 6, if they lived near power lines in the
first two years of life. 500 words.
