<P>
   CHRONICLE-SALE (San Francisco) _ In a move that could result in
dramatic changes in the San Francisco area's media marketplace,
owners of the San Francisco Chronicle and KRON-TV have authorized
the sale of the newspaper and TV station and other assets.
Chronicle editors said the step was part of a process that would
take months to unfold. By EMILY GURNON, JULIAN GUTHRIE and SCOTT
WINOKUR.
</P>
<P>
   DOLE-VEEP (San Jose, Calif.) _ Tired of suggestions that she
would make a good vice presidential nominee to GOP front-runner
George W. Bush, Elizabeth Dole says she isn't interested in the No.
2 spot. ``You would not undertake this sort of rigorous process in
order to be vice president,'' Dole said. ``You do it to win. I'm in
it to win.'' By ZACHARY COILE.
</P>
