   ENTERTAINMENT (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-REVIEW-TARZAN (Undated) _ In the 87-year-career of Tarzan,
the Lord of the Apes, he has been attacked by leopards, shot at by
hunters, seduced by ladies, belittled by fops and chased along the
Brooklyn Bridge. And now, he's been Disneyed. This might have been
a good thing. But there are two elements missing in the new
``Tarzan'' movie: Characters and plot. By AMY BIANCOLLI.
</P>
<P>
   TARZAN-TRADITION (Undated) _ Call him Monkey Boy. Call him Vine
Man. Call him Lord of the Jungle, Lord of the Apes or Lord of the
Loincloth. But whatever you call him, he's back _ Tarzan, poster
boy for the 20th-century's deep aboriginal urge. By AMY BIANCOLLI.
</P>
