doesn't have to be a two-hour, labor-intensive ordeal. To be sure,
you can have all kinds of fun making a tangy sauce from scratch for
marinating and basting chicken and other meats. And odds are it
will be better than almost anything available in the grocery store.
By DOUG BLACKBURN.
