<P>
   &UR; FROM HERE TO ETERNITY: THE LATEST HIGH-TECH TELESCOPES &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; THREE COLOR SLIDES ARE AVAILABLE FREE &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,000 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By MICHAEL D. LEMONICK &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Japan's wafer-thin 8.3-meter Subaru telescope collected its
first images from space in January. The Gemini North, an 8.1-meter
telescope built by a seven-nation consortium that includes the
United States, is scheduled to begin scanning the heavens any day.
These telescopes are part of the elite new generation of optics
that promises to lead mankind beyond the solar system into
unexplored regions of space. Michael D. Lemonick, a senior science
writer at Time, reports.
</P>
<P>
   slugged: BC-OTHERWORDLY-VIEWS-NYTSF. Sent to category codes
``a'' general news and ``l'' lifestyle news.
