   &UR; DEADLY KNEE BENDS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; ONE COLOR SLIDE IS AVAILABLE FREE &QL; 
 &UR; (1,100 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By TONY DAJER &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   When Mr. Kelly said his legs were killing him, he was right. A
prisoner in New York City jail, Mr. Kelly participated in a deep
knee-bend competition judged by fellow inmates. His winning lift:
1,134 pounds. What he didn't realize was the damage he had done to
his leg muscles _ and consequently his kidneys. Tony Dajer, who is
at work on a book about medical mistakes and the science of
diagnosis, reports.
</P>
