<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HIT-ROADRAGE18-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Pedestrian struck twice in road rage
 &HT;    By A. Scharnhorst
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ A driver was so angry at a pedestrian
who cursed her that she turned her car around, ran into the woman
and then made another U-turn to ram the pedestrian head-on,
investigators said.
</P>
<P>
   Laura Boone, 38, of suburban West Palm Beach, suffered two
broken legs and other injuries in the hit-and-run, officials said.
She was in fair condition at Delray Medical Center on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Boone was walking with a friend along the sidewalk when a small
white car drove by heading east, reports show. She began cursing at
the driver and ``ran out into the roadway taunting the car,'' said
sheriff's Det. Tom Becksfort.
</P>
<P>
   Detectives did not know why Boone swore at the driver or what
she said, but a friend told investigators it ``is not uncommon for
her to do something like that,'' Becksfort said.
</P>
<P>
   While her friend yelled at her to get back on the sidewalk, the
car turned around on the same side of the street and struck Boone
in a glancing blow, Becksfort said. The driver did another U-turn
and drove back to strike Boone again.
</P>
<P>
   ``She bounced up on the hood and rolled off'' over the top of
the car, Becksfort said.
</P>
<P>
   The driver was described as a white woman with frizzy blond
hair, accompanied by a Hispanic woman. She may have been driving a
Ford Escort, witnesses told police.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
