<P>
   WITH: TRAVEL BRIEFS -- Visitors to Rhode Island this summer will
have a chance to tour a variety of gardens, big and small, during
the first annual Gardens Open for Blithewold tour. (Staff, N.Y.
Times News Service)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: ZOO DESTINATIONS -- Want to get really ``wild'' this
summer? We're not talking about beer blasts on the beach or
skinny-dipping by the light of the August moon. We're talking about
locking eyes with a 400-pound gorilla. (Hamilton, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-INNS _ Bed and breakkfast inns are often referred to as
country inns because so many are quaint little getaways in the
mountains or countryside, away from the hustle and bustle of big
cities or popular vacation resorts. But some are springing up in
beach towns, providing guests that charming feel of being in the
countryside with all the sundrenched opportunities that go along
with being at the beach. Two fine examples are in the midst of
celebrated, Southeast vacation spots: Henderson Park Inn in Destin,
Fla. on the Forida panhandle, and Elizabeth Pointe Lodge Amelia
Island in Northeast Florida. (Laccetti Meyers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)WITH PHOTOS .
</P>
<P>
   EDS: EMBARGOED FOR SUNDAY, JUNE 20.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-INNVISIT _ Visits to two beachside Fla. B&AMP;Bs: Henderson
Park Inn in Destin and Elizabeth Pointe Lodge on Amelia Island In
Northeast Florida.(Laccetti Meyers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EDS: EMBARGOED FOR SUNDAY, JUNE 20.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-LASTMINUTE _ The best kind of travel is the last-minute
kind, booked online. At least that's what the Atlanta founders of
LastMinuteTravel.com soon will be trying to convince travelers
across the nation. Their fledgling web site _ now in a limited
``sneak preview'' mode _ links spur-of-the-moment travelers with
airlines, hotels and other suppliers that have unsold inventory to
unload online. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This story moved Tuesday in the (f) Financial category.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY _ Savannah works its charms on everyone who comes to
visit, even giggly Girl Scouts who came to the city primarily to
visit the Low House _ now officially the Juliette Gordon Low Girl
Scout National Center. The antebellum mansion nestled under red
oaks and Spanish moss at the corner of Bull and Oglethorpe Streets
is definitely not just for Girl Scouts. Low story is accompanied by
detailed If You Go to help plan a summer visit to Savannah. (Kloer,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY-FESTIVALS _ Southern happenings. (Thrasher, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION
</P>
<P>
   MIRACLE-BRA _Va va va click! For those who think the Miracle Bra
isn't miraculous enough, the Wonder Bra not wonderful enough,
there's a new way to boost your bust. The Miracle Click Bra, new
from Victoria's Secret, lets you click your way to a bigger
bustline. Want big? Click once. Bigger? Twice. Spilling out of the
dress? Make it a threefer. (Lee, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   STYLE-FACIALHAIR _ RAZOR SHARP _ Style centerpiece focusing on
facial hair, how Atlanta men groom their beards and moustaches and
why. Also, remarks from women on likes/dislikes. (AHill, Atlanta
journal-Constitution). WITH COLOR PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed for Sunday, June 20.
</P>
