   FASHION-TIES _ Father's Day classics: Neckties offer a
traditional Father's Day gift solution but non-traditional designs
are 'knot' to be ignored. Copy block with photos of statues wearing
ties. (Janjigian, Palm Beach Daily News). WITH COLOR PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moved Saturday, June 12.
</P>
<P>
   HOME AND GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   LEEMAY-ZINNIAS _ Day after day, Lee May goes to his garden to
monitor the progress of his would-be zinnia patch. Day after day,
he marvels that any plant could reach such a sad plateau and remain
poised there, not growing taller, yet not giving up and falling
down, either. (May, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HYDRANGEAS _ Penny McHenry, 74, has been dubbed Atlanta's
``Hydrangea Lady.'' With more than 400 of her ``girls'' in place,
McHenry's garden has been billed one of the country's finest
hydrangea collections. If that wasn't, enough McHenry is the
founder of American Hydrangea Society. (Flanders, Atlanta
Journal-Consitution). WITH COLOR PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   PIRATES-HALL _ A few questions for actor Anthony Michael Hall,
who portrays Bill Gates in TNT's ``Pirates of Silicon Valley,''
debuting Sunday (June 20). (Jubera, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
10.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   PIRATES-WYLE _ A few questions for actor Noah Wyle, who portrays
Steve Jobs in TNT's ``Pirates of Silicon Valley,'' debuting Sunday
(June 20). (Jubera, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVOLTA _ A collection of items about John Travolta, whose new
shot-in-Savannah movie ``The General's Daughter'' opens this day.
Included will be a detailed videography and his thoughts about
working in Savannah. (Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 31.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-TARZAN _ Review of ``Tarzan,'' Disney's effective and
visually groundbreaking (background technique gives it a 3-D look)
new animated movie. It's no ``Beauty and the Beast'' but kids will
undoubtedly love it. It's fast-paced, funny and, in the best
tradition of Disney, handles death scenes with appropriate
restraint for young eyes. Grade: B+. (BLongino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   TARZAN-CD _ Review of Tarzan. (Eldredge, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 3.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-INNOCENCE _ Movie review of new ``Loss of Sexual
Innocence'' from Mike Figgis (''Leaving Las Vegas''), a study of
not only the loss of sexual innocence but all innocence. Grade: B-.
(Ringel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-YESTERDAY _ Douglas Henshall plays Victor, a wreck of a
London actor pining for the girlfriend he lost a year ago. That's
when Sylvia (Lena Headey) found out about his fling with an
actress, and quickly tumbled into love with a man she's met at her
health club, David (Mark Strong). (StMurray, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED TUESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-BUENA _ If you're not already a fan of the crossover hit
record, ``Buena Vista Social Club,'' you might feel lost during the
documentary that bears the same name. Shot by German auteur Wim
Wenders, the movie follows musician Ry Cooder and his son Joachim
back to Cuba, where he rediscovered the near-forgotten musical
artists of the pre-Castro era. (StMurray, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED TUESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BUENA-COODER _ Interview with Ry Cooder about docu ``Buena Vista
Social Club.'' (Dollar, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-MINIREVIEWS _ Movie roundup: John Travolta's military
thriller ``The General's Daughter'' (Grade: C-); Cuban music film
``The Buena Vista Social Club'' (Grade: B-) and ``Get Real'' (a
British film involving the angst of gay teen love; Grade: C-).
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
