<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Allure for Men, Romance take top fragrance honors
 &HT;    Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, June 20
 &HT;    By A. Scott Walton
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Every year, the New York-based Fragrance Foundation makes a big
stink over its FiFi Awards. At this annual gala, industry leaders
hail the scents most pleasing to their sensibilities.
</P>
<P>
   The 1999 awards were handed out earlier this month, and the U.S.
Men's Fragrance Star of the Year award went to Chanel's Allure for
Men. The other two nominees in that category were Calvin Klein's
Contradiction and Gucci's Envy for Men.
</P>
<P>
   In accepting the award, Laurie Palma, a giddy Chanel executive,
said, ``This is such a thrilling moment for us. In 1997 we took
home a FiFi for Allure for Women, and winning one this year for
Allure for Men is a true testament to the power of Allure.''
</P>
<P>
   In the oversexed advertising environment we live in, the
marketing campaign for Allure is rather novel. Its black-and-white
print ads feature nine men who have achieved a measure of success
in their fields but who are not instantly recognizable. Each is
identified only by his profession and hometown. A line underneath
reads, ``Real men. Real allure.'' Beneath that is a phrase
illustrating the intrigue of each man, such as ``Sex appeal is just
the beginning.''
</P>
<P>
   The Allure for Men scent combines sensual, woody, spicy and
fresh fragrance notes such as fruity bergamot, citron zest,
vetiver, high atlas cedar, tonka bean and hot Jamaican pepper.
Allure products range in price from $32.50 to $48.50.
</P>
<P>
   Other major FiFi Awards went to Ralph Lauren's Romance (U.S.
Women's Fragrance Star of the Year); Cacharel's NOA (European
Women's Star Fragrance); Emporio Armani (European Men's Star
Fragrance); and Van Cleef &AMP; Arpel's First (Fragrance Hall of Fame).
</P>
<P>
   _ A. Scott Walton writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
