<P>
   SOCCER
</P>
<P>
   SOC-MIAHAMM _ She's been called one of the most beautiful people
in the world, but it wasn't her idea. Appearing in a Gatorade
commercial with Michael Jordan is a good way to promote her sport,
as far as she's concerned. And the way she sees it, all the media
hysteria over a recent goal drought took away from the rest of the
team. Nike just named its biggest building after her, but she was
red-faced about the whole thing. The attention devoted to U.S.
soccer star Mia Hamm has spawned out of her phenomenal career for
the defending Olympic champions, who are setting their sights on
the Women's World Cup that begins Saturday. But the 27-year-old
forward's attractiveness has evolved into a ``Mia Mania'' that
causes teenage girls to shriek and men to wonder just who the lucky
guy is who's married to her. Hamm's passion shows most on the
field, where she recently became the all-time international
goal-scoring leader, but the extremely shy wife of a U.S. Marine
pilot is finding how difficult it is becoming to seek private
refuge away from it. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 16.
</P>
<P>
   SOC-CUP-NOTES _ Notebook items from U.S. training camp in New
Jersey, other Women's World Cup d evelopments. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
<P>
   RACING
</P>
<P>
   COXNET NASCAR PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDs: The CoxNet NASCAR page will be available Thursday at 3 p.m.
EDT.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET NASCAR 0618: GORDON ON TRACK _ With back-to-back seconds,
Jeff Gordon appears to be getting things back on track. But he has
only picked up five points on leader Dale Jarrett and has all but
conceded that he won't catch him in the points race. (Schlabach,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   w/WINSTON CUP NOTES _ Odds and ends file from Winston Cup.
(Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   IN THE PITS _ Column on Winston Cup happenings off the track.
Art includes two thumbs up/thumbs down illustrations.
</P>
<P>
   TRACK GRAPHIC _ A 2-column color illustration of Pocono Raceway.
</P>
