</P>
<P>
   END OF PAGE
</P>
<P>
   LEMONDROP-OWNERS _ Jeanne Vance and Milton 'Laddie' Dance,
owners of Lemon Drop Kid, live in Manalapan (near Palm Beach). They
are interviewed about their excitement _ and disbelief _ in winning
the Belmont. The couple has a long history in the horse industry,
which brought them together. (Gelormine, Palm Beach Daily News).
WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-JAMAL _ Falcons RB Jamal Anderson discusses contract
situation, life away from passing camp, his love for the Falcons
and head coach Dan Reeves and why he's looking for big bucks in a
wide-ranging Q&AMP;A. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   w/FBN-FALCONS-CAP _In the wake of their Super Bowl season, the
Falcons will have to do some expert maneuvering with the NFL's
salary cap to keep the team in tact. With nine starters approaching
the end of their contracts, Atlanta had the second per-player
salary average in the NFC during the 1998 season. Expect more of
the same in 1999. As GM Harold Richardson says, it's the cost of
success. (Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
