their withdrawal from the south of Kosovo, the NATO-led
peacekeeping forces have been slow to move into the west of the
province, creating a vacuum of authority and the mass reverse
exodus of Serb civilians fearing revenge from the Kosovo Liberation
Army. But after the Bishop of Rasca and Prizren fled the city for
his safety on Wednesday, despite the presence of German troops,
NATO and United Nations officials today moved into higher gear to
try to contain the damage to their reputation for impartiality. By
Steven Erlanger.
