   KOSOVO-GRAVES (Qyshk, Yugoslavia) _ In a little over two hours
of wandering in three small villages near the city of Pec, it
became clear that anyone you asked could point you to graves or
places where Kosovo's Albanian civilians had been killed by Serbs.
The accounts in this tiny corner of Kosovo, emerging as Kosovo
Albanians return to their homes and as journalists and human rights
workers begin to range through the shattered province, suggest that
the death toll and the carnage may be even greater than previously
known. By John Kifner.
</P>
