   KUWAIT-VOTE (Kuwait City) _ Until three weeks ago, the law that
laid out who could vote and seek office began ``Each Kuwaiti man.''
Subject to ratification by the next Parliament, it now begins `Each
Kuwaiti.'' The change, which shocked even its supporters, would
bring an end to an era in which political life has been an all-male
preserve. By Douglas Jehl.
