   BORDER-BABIES (Brownsville, Texas) _ Griselda Vidrio thought
there was something oddly familiar about the smile on the infant a
Honduran woman was clutching in her arms at the Border Patrol's
illegal-alien processing center in Brownsville. Sure enough, when
officials looked into it they discovered that the same baby had
been used as a prop by phony parents on at least three and probably
many more occasions. Smugglers had discovered an inadvertent,
humanitarian loophole in the increasingly difficult game of begging
people across the Rio Grande and into the United States. By Rick
Lyman.
