<SLUG> BC-COX-MIRACLE-BRA18 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Clicking for cleavage the latest in bra technology
 &HT;    By Elizabeth Lee
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Va-va-va click! For women who think the Miracle Bra
isn't miraculous enough, the Wonderbra not wonderful enough,
there's a new way to boost the bustline.
</P>
<P>
   The Click Miracle Bra, new from Victoria's Secret, lets you snap
your way to cleavage that would look right at home in a Mark Eden
ad. Or at least that's the theory.
</P>
<P>
   Want big? Click to tighten the front fastener. Eye-popping?
Click twice. Spilling out of the dress? Make it a threefer.
</P>
<P>
   The bra, introduced a month ago, is the top-selling item in
Victoria Secret's catalog. In stores, it's selling about the same
as other bras, says Monica Mitro, vice president for public
relations for the lingerie company.
</P>
<P>
   It's selling despite the fact that, at $42, the Click Miracle is
the most expensive bra the chain stocks. So far, Victoria's Secret
is the only U.S. outlet for this latest weapon in the
cleavage-enhancement arsenal.
</P>
<P>
   ``Wow,'' said 18-year-old Amanda Calvert of Duluth (Ga.), who
was browsing through the Perimeter Mall store this week. She said
the Click Miracle was a cool idea, but reconsidered after learning
the price. ``Depends on how much cleavage you get out of it.''
</P>
<P>
   Here's how it works: Underwires and removable pads push breasts
inward and upward. The click mechanism, front and center in the
bra, pulls the cups even closer together. You can click on purpose
or, if you're hugging your arms together, blossom unintentionally
but not inaudibly.
</P>
<P>
   ``You just have to be aware when you're wearing it of those
drastic arm movements,'' says Mitro, who road-tested the bra along
with other Victoria's Secret employees. ``Around the office you
could hear the little clicks going.''
</P>
<P>
   Calvert, already a Wonderbra wearer, decided to give the latest
technology a try. Her mother, Mary, 44, watched in the dressing
room. When mom suggested she tighten the bra again _ after she'd
already clicked the maximum three times _ Calvert hung it up.
</P>
<P>
   ``It gave me some cleavage,'' she said, ``but not enough.''
</P>
<P>
   Elizabeth Lee writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
