   CORRECTION: Photos NYT2 and NYT3 from 06/07/99 that accompanied
the story ENRIQUE-MARTINEZ misidentified the subject. The subject
of both photos is a model who is not unidentified. A portrait of
the owner of the fashion house Enrique Martinez, Elisa Salinas, is
moving tonight as NYT4.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT34) KOKOMO, Ind. -- June 17, 1999 -- PAYDAY-LOANS, 6-17 -- A
product of the nation's most prosperous peacetime decade in this
century, payday lending concerns are sprouting up across the
country, with 8,000 today against 300 seven years ago; this one is
in Kokomo. To obtain a loan at a payday lending company, a borrower
writes a cheick for the amount of the loan plus the loan fee, and
the check is held until the borrowers' next payday. (Mary Ann
Carter/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
