<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Friday, June 18. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
COLUMBINE (Phoenix) _ Brooks Brown would rather be identified as
the best debater in Phoenix this week than as the controversial
friend of the two Littleton, Colorado gunmen. But as he stood
outside the Tempe conference room where he is competing in the
national high school debate championships, even the Arizona heat
couldn't distract him from thinking about that cold day when he
lost four of his friends. He's one of 2,300 high school students
participating in the National Forensic League's Desert Sun National
Speech and Debate Tournament this week. This year he's the
tournament's best-known competitior _ for reasons he and his
teammates would rather forget. Brown even selected Columbine as a
subject to debate at the tournament. BY M. BRADFORD GRABOWSKI.
Story will move in the A category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
