 &QL; 
OK (Undated) _ More than a century after the gun smoke cleared,
Americans still are fascinated. Movies, books, Web sites _ all
still wrestle with the enduring controversy surrounding one of the
most famous shootouts in the Wild West. The gunfight at the OK
Corral in Tombstone took 27 seconds and about 30 shots. Three
people died. Doc Holliday and Wyatt Earp were arrested but never
tried. Until now. Next week, prominent Arizona attorneys and judges
will stage a public ``trial'' to determine what really happened in
that rowdy southern Arizona mining town in 1881. By VICTORIA
