<SLUG> BC-BBN-BRAVES-ASTROS18-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Millwood perfectly fine vs. Astros
 &HT;    By Carroll Rogers
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ Forget that they've been the most consistent starters
for the top two pitching staffs in the National League. The
strikingly different personalities of Kevin Millwood and Jose Lima
are what made Thursday night's game interesting.
</P>
<P>
   Millwood's laid-back style won out over Lima and his
demonstrative act on the mound in the Braves' 8-5 win. Millwood
flirted with a no-hitter for the second time in his last three
starts, struck out a season-high 11 and drove in two runs.
</P>
<P>
   An early exchange over an errant Millwood pitch up and in to
Lima gave the game an undercurrent that added to a meeting between
division leaders.
</P>
<P>
   As the Braves won the series 3-1, Millwood backed up wins by Tom
Glavine and Greg Maddux by outpitching both of them, which wasn't
easy to do. He had a perfect game through six innings before giving
up back-to-back singles to Craig Biggio and Bill Spiers to start
the seventh. The Astros broke up the shutout that inning on a
run-scoring fielder's choice by Carl Everett and a Millwood wild
pitch.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, the Braves offense took out a little of its hitting
frustation on Lima, the National League's winningest pitcher this
year with 11. Atlanta piled up 10 hits and a season-high seven runs
against him and ended his night after six innings.
</P>
<P>
   Javy Lopez matched his career high with four hits, including a
home run and two RBIs.
</P>
<P>
   With memories of last Saturday's first-inning pounding by
Baltimore fresh in his mind, Millwood worked the first inning
against Houston very carefully. He struck out Jeff Bagwell on three
pitches, and continued that trend by setting down the next 15
batters. Not until Biggio lined his first pitch of the seventh into
center was the no-no done.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
